README Proposal for 
**Agentic AI Secretary Chip (AISC)**

Executive Summary : A compact USB‑based Agentic AI Secretary Chip (AISC) , AI device that autonomously captures meeting audio/video/screen, generates minutes, 
extracts action items, drafts follow‑ups, and integrates with enterprise tools. All AI processing is done on‑device using an NPU/TPU for privacy and low latency.
Once plugged in, it autonomously accesses the computer’s microphone, camera, and screen (with user permission) to:
- Capture meeting audio/video
- Extract meeting minutes
- Identify action items
- Draft follow‑up emails
- Sync tasks with productivity tools
- Provide real‑time meeting assistance
Unlike cloud‑only AI tools, AISC offers on‑device processing, enterprise‑grade privacy, and zero‑setup deployment, making it ideal for corporations, consultants, and remote workers.


Core Benefits
- Plug‑and‑play: No installation, no IT overhead
- Privacy-first: On-device LLM inference
- Cross-platform: Windows, macOS, Linux
- Agentic autonomy: AI acts proactively
- Enterprise-ready: Encryption, audit logs, admin controls


